										<td colspan=2 valign="top">
										<div align=left><br><font class='header2'>Q & A Session</font><font class='small'>&nbsp;by randerson at 7/19/2000 6:53:00 PM PST</font><blockquote class='normal'><FONT size=2>
<P>Gordon 'Abashi' Wrinn visited an EverQuest fan chat room this evening to hold a long Q &amp; A session directly with the players. He also goes on to announce the status of the servers and when they are expected up, as we recently reported. Here is a small portion of the session, please click continue to view the full thing. Brought to you by EQanswers.com first!</P>
<P align=center><STRONG><FONT color=gold>Q &amp; A Session with Abashi</FONT></STRONG></P></FONT>
<P><EM>&lt;Ivern&gt; Abashi: sorry if you've been asked this already, but when are the new dragons going to go live? :)</EM><BR><BR><STRONG><FONT color=gold>&lt;Abashi&gt;</FONT></STRONG> Ivern: Dragons? What dragons :)</P>
<P><EM>&lt;Uglar&gt; Abashi, can we sue Verant if we get lung cancer from smoking while playing eq?&nbsp; =)</EM><BR><BR><STRONG><FONT color=gold>&lt;Abashi&gt;</FONT></STRONG> Uglar: You can sue anyone for anything, whether you get laughed out of court and whether your attorney gets sanctioned is antoher matter :)</P>
<P><EM>&lt;Jalapeno&gt; Abashi: can something be done so procs (jboots, staff or writhing's chaotic feedback) doesn't falsely recharge the harvest icon before the 10 min recharge?</EM><BR><BR><STRONG><FONT color=gold>&lt;Abashi&gt;</FONT></STRONG> Jalapeno: I wasn't aware that anything of that nature was happening?How's it done? ~<BR><BR><EM>&lt;Jalapeno&gt; Abashi: it doesn't let you recast harvest, just the icon ungreys after a proc, makes it hard to know when you can use it unless you have clocked how long ago you cast harvest</EM><BR><BR><STRONG><FONT color=gold>&lt;Abashi&gt;</FONT></STRONG> So after 10 minutes you can still cast it but the icon is grayed?<BR><BR><EM>&lt;Jalapeno&gt; icon ungreys<BR></EM><BR><STRONG><FONT color=gold>&lt;Abashi&gt;</FONT></STRONG> Oh, ok, I'll mention that one... </P>
<P><EM><FONT color=white>&lt;Uglar&gt;</FONT> &lt;tada&gt; Another question... Why do the other class specific armor/item quests in sol temple give exp, but the cleric quests do not?</EM><BR><BR><STRONG><FONT color=gold>&lt;Abashi&gt;</FONT></STRONG> tada: In some cases we removed the expernece on a quest in order to keep epople who weren't of that class from farming the items and depriving them from the class they were meant for.I'm not sure whether that happened with those quests or not, I'll check into it</P>
<P><EM>&lt;jason`cmu&gt; Have they even looked into the decay time of uber-bosses, ie Dracolich, defeated him, came back, got mobed by an assling, corpse decayed in 5 mins with a no drop warrior sword.</EM><BR><BR><STRONG><FONT color=gold>&lt;Abashi&gt;</FONT></STRONG> Jason'cmu: We elected not to extend the decay times.&nbsp; /roll faster :)&nbsp; </P>
<P><EM>&lt;Loki--&gt; got a lot of questions about cleric armor</EM><BR><BR><STRONG><FONT color=gold>&lt;Abashi&gt;</FONT></STRONG> Loki: I don't want to talk about cleric armor :)&nbsp;<BR><BR><EM>&lt;Loki--&gt; hehe<BR></EM><BR><STRONG><FONT color=gold>&lt;Abashi&gt;</FONT></STRONG> Er, I should say that I don't know it well enough to speak about specific pieces.</P>
<P><EM><FONT color=white>&lt;Baelish&gt;</FONT> Abashi Any ETA yet on ficing the mez stackig and slow stacking bugs?</EM><BR><BR><STRONG><FONT color=gold>&lt;Abashi&gt;</FONT></STRONG> Baelish: Not yet, I've been wanting to bring it up again but we've had a lot of other things that have been going on lately.</P>
<P><EM>&lt;frash&gt; *dav_d* will the /assist a_mob00 to know if the mob is up in zone will be fixed someday?</EM><BR>&nbsp; <BR><STRONG><FONT color=gold>&lt;Abashi&gt;</FONT></STRONG> dav_d: Strangely enough, I believe that it was fixed this patch.</P>
<P><EM>&lt;Crus&gt; Abashi, got a question for ya... You said People would lose just as much exp in 45 as 46... Well.. In 45, I died and lost 1/4th a bubble of exp.. Then later on I dinged to 46, and died pretty much immediately, I then lost 3/4ths out of 45</EM><BR><BR><STRONG><FONT color=gold>&lt;Abashi&gt;</FONT></STRONG> Crus: The original information that I released about XP loss was incorrect.&nbsp; I finally got it all sorted out a few months ago, but haven't gone out of my way to address those threads yet.<BR><BR><STRONG><FONT color=gold>&lt;Abashi&gt;</FONT></STRONG> Crus: Experience loss is based on the total experience needed by a human warrior to complete the PREVIOUS level.&nbsp; So, you lose less (relative to level) in 30, and more in 31.</P>
<P><EM>&lt;`Davey&gt; Abashi, I have a problem, If you can reply to this question that would be great, Yesterday Night I was cleared 1/2 of fear, Then all of the sudden, our repops in front of us, and killed us all, I may say, That was a zone repop, but the GM did not warn us, we all Petitioned, and got no answer, a GM was going anon alot, Thank god after the patch the plane was empty, so I had a chance to get my corpse, just wondering can that happen?err, CT repopped I meant.</EM><BR><BR><STRONG><FONT color=gold>&lt;Abashi&gt;</FONT></STRONG> `Davey: Seems to me that I saw a post on Flameplay about that today, didn't I?&nbsp; Sometimes zones are repopped spontaneously by the system.&nbsp; If that happens, first, everything will disappear, then over about 1 minute the zone will competely fill back up<BR><BR><STRONG><FONT color=gold>&lt;Abashi&gt;</FONT></STRONG> `davey: Did pets in yoru group *poof* as well?<BR><BR><EM>&lt;`Davey&gt; Yes</EM><BR><BR><STRONG><FONT color=gold>&lt;Abashi&gt;</FONT></STRONG> `davey: That must have been what happened.&nbsp; It can be a pain, espicially in the planes.</P>
<P><EM>&lt;DaScott&gt; Abashi: are you aware that the three best damage dealing weapons in the game are the barbed whip, moss covered twig, and moss covered branch in frontier mountains on level 30 mobs? Because of the main-hand damage bonus, these weapons outdamage ALL weapons in the game<BR></EM><BR><STRONG><FONT color=gold>&lt;Abashi&gt;</FONT></STRONG> DaScott: A new game designer went a little nuts with those items, forgot the min-damage calculation. They actually won't drop any more.&nbsp; We're considering leaving the existing ones as-is.<BR><BR><EM>&lt;DaScott&gt; Abashi: and someone caught this, nerfed it to 4/12 (which by the way is still better than anything in higher level dungeons) and it was changed BACK? Simple solution: remove branch, make others offhand only, or just grandfather them</EM><BR><BR><EM>&lt;DaScott&gt; Abashi: heh thanks for confirmation</EM><BR><BR><STRONG><FONT color=gold>&lt;Abashi&gt;</FONT></STRONG> DaScott: Well, the nerf/unnerf was a different sittuation, but the solution you mention is simple, of course you know how much grief we take for 'always nerfing'</P>
<P><EM>&lt;discore&gt; Abashi: (i hope its my turn!hehe) have you fixed failed binds? i havent tested lately, but 3 weeks ago i could make a bind fail.</EM><BR><BR><STRONG><FONT color=gold>&lt;Abashi&gt;</FONT></STRONG> Discore: I dont' think that they've been able to reproduce that one on test yet, but cant' say for sure.&nbsp; Stop by the QA board and tell Ester.</P>
<P><EM>&lt;Uglar&gt; &lt;PlzRolbak&gt; hi. one of the things that was said to be done in the patch was that the spellbook icons and gems were to updated. all i knoticed is one of my dd spells got an evocation icon (red hand) insted of the tornado icon it used to have. is more planned to be done?</EM><BR><BR><STRONG><FONT color=gold>&lt;Abashi&gt;</FONT></STRONG> PlzRolbak: Some of them were really messed up.&nbsp; It's also possible that they all didn't make it in this patch, which is why I didnt' name spells.&nbsp; There were actually about 70 gem/icon changes</P>
<P><EM><FONT color=white>&lt;frash&gt;</FONT> Abashi: When are girl bards gunna dance ? We are the masters of song and dance. ANd girl ones dont dance. It should be the MEN who dont dance, just like IRL</EM><BR><BR><STRONG><FONT color=gold>&lt;Abashi&gt;</FONT></STRONG> Frash: The anims are a pain to put in post-production.&nbsp; We lost a few when loading in all of the new ones when we put them in.&nbsp; We hope to pop the missing ones back in sometime in the future.</P>
<P><EM>&lt;FritoLays&gt; Abashi: Can you nerf magicians so people will stop playing them and the true skillful mages emerge to the top again to replace the powerleveling skill-lacking ones?</EM><BR><BR><STRONG><FONT color=gold>&lt;Abashi&gt;</FONT></STRONG> Frito: Er, I think I'll pass on that one :)</P>
<P><EM>&lt;jason`cmu&gt; Abashi: a month or so again, there was minor patches pertaining to the music in the game, such as adding a few zones with music with the plans in the future of updating all the zones, i havn't seen anymore patches of this nature.&nbsp; Have those plans been scraped?&nbsp; Also, is there any future plans to add more music to the game?&nbsp; Maybe some talented music players can create some music for the kunark zones finally</EM><BR><BR><STRONG><FONT color=gold>&lt;Abashi&gt;</FONT></STRONG> Jason: They are on hold pending release of the new sound engine.&nbsp; That should be in a few weeks, then we can start looking at more sounds again.</P>
<P><EM>&lt;frash&gt; *daxdon* can you ask him how he and the live team feel about mage pets post 50 and if there are any plans or changes inthe mix for them?</EM>&nbsp;<BR><BR><STRONG><FONT color=gold>&lt;Abashi&gt;</FONT></STRONG> Daxdon: No plans at present to revisit those pets.&nbsp; They might not be much stronger on a linear basis compared to the level 49 ones, but pets overall are already stronger than we would like.&nbsp; </P>
<P><EM>&lt;Uglar&gt; Abashi:&nbsp; You said before the patch/dev team was working on a plan of action, any updates as to what they have come up with yet?</EM><BR><BR><STRONG><FONT color=gold>&lt;Abashi&gt;</FONT></STRONG> Uglar: Nope, not yet, sorry :(</P>
<P><EM>&lt;Baelish&gt; &lt;Zumar-Eci&gt; can you ask this question please.... I have been camping emperor chottal for about a month off and on whenever a rogue is avaliable to try to get my 59 necro pet, but most of the time it only drops 60 spells, is this how it should be?</EM><BR><BR><STRONG><FONT color=gold>&lt;Abashi&gt;</FONT></STRONG> Zumar: I'd consider trying a different zone.&nbsp; Not every spell drops in every zone, you might have to hunt around a bit.</P>
<P><EM>&lt;frash&gt; *Nikster* can you relay ... are there still known problems with the sound blaster live cards and everquest? i have the updated drivers... yet i tend to get a blue screen once a night stating an EAX error? <BR></EM><BR><STRONG><FONT color=gold>&lt;Abashi&gt;</FONT></STRONG> Nikster: Some players report problems, the new sound engine should fix up the problem.</P>
<P><EM>&lt;Hidaglio&gt; Abashi: Xerxes-Veeshan: Why does the lvl 56 necro pet have a higher max hit than the lvl 59 pet</EM><BR><BR><STRONG><FONT color=gold>&lt;Abashi&gt;</FONT></STRONG> Xerxes: SpectreLifetap and SpectreStun?<BR><BR><EM>&lt;frash&gt; *Viron_X* Hey, I got a question for Abashi, if you dont mind...&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; When a group member loggs or gets dced you cant kick them or disban the group and your group has to logg out. This is very annoying, will it be fixed ever?</EM> <BR><BR><STRONG><FONT color=gold>&lt;Abashi&gt;</FONT></STRONG> Viron: We're going to fix those group bugs.&nbsp; One of them went in today (DC while zoning hosing the group), the rest are probab ly going ot be int eh next patch.</P>
<P><EM>&lt;Hidaglio&gt; Abashi: When you added the new 'High Level' rogue poisons, are you talking better DD/DOT or less resistant poisons for fighting bigger creatures?<BR></EM><BR><STRONG><FONT color=gold>&lt;Abashi&gt;</FONT></STRONG> Hidaglio: About 10 new poisons, which require more skill and do more damage.&nbsp; I believe that the top DOt does over 700 damage.</P>
<P><EM>&lt;frash&gt; *Ranador* Abashi: was the ranger damage bug relatively minor in the sense we wont notice a difference ? and is defenseive ability being discussed as was said by JB and Brad at the gatherin in Vegas<BR></EM><BR><STRONG><FONT color=gold>&lt;Abashi&gt;</FONT></STRONG> Ranador: It's not that big of a difference, since ranger damage tables were already close to the warriors.&nbsp; As for the defense issue that have been brought up, we're still considering everything.&nbsp; We can only make one change at a time and let it sink in in order to get an idea what is *really* going on.</P>
<P><EM>&lt;frash&gt; *[FruxX]* Question: Will enchanters ever be able to cast enthrall/mez over AE mez without it 'not taking hold', or will we always have to wait for ae mez to break first?</EM>&nbsp; <BR><BR><STRONG><FONT color=gold>&lt;Abashi&gt;</FONT></STRONG> Fruxx: It's still on the list, sorry about the stacking problem with mez and the 'insects' line.&nbsp; </P>
<P><EM>&lt;Hidaglio&gt; Abashi: Fiae-Veeshan: Thank you, are resists lowered on higher damage poison?</EM><BR><BR><STRONG><FONT color=gold>&lt;Abashi&gt;</FONT></STRONG> Hidaglio: No change to resist rates were made.&nbsp; It all depends on your levle versus the level of the creature, and it's poison resist.</P>
<P><EM>&lt;frash&gt; p*Drazen* When there is a moment, can you ask if there will be a fix put in that allows LD people to be healed? Nuthin worse then watching your Groupmate die while LD cause you cant heal em.</EM>&nbsp; <BR><BR><STRONG><FONT color=gold>&lt;Abashi&gt;</FONT></STRONG> Drazen: No, we disallowed it purposely due to some exploits that were available when linkdead, and some current advantages in game for being linkdead.&nbsp; Basically we don't want linkdeath to ever be a desirable condition.<BR><BR><STRONG><FONT color=gold>&lt;Abashi&gt;</FONT></STRONG> Drazen: No, we disallowed it purposely due to some exploits that were available when linkdead, and some current advantages in game for being linkdead.&nbsp; Basically we don't want linkdeath to ever be a desirable condition.</P>
<P><EM>&lt;frash&gt; *YukiTaro* I'd like to hear on why so many items are removed from the game, ie : Gem Encrusted Ring, Rod of Mourning, Idol of the Thorned and now the moss covered weapons</EM><BR><BR><STRONG><FONT color=gold>&lt;Abashi&gt;</FONT></STRONG> YukiTare: Sometimes they are removed just because they get old, and there are enough in the world.&nbsp; Ohter times, they are removed because they are too powerful.&nbsp;&nbsp; Standard practice is to remove the drop and replace it with something that is balanced, assumign we don't modify the item itself.&nbsp; </P>
<P><EM>&lt;Uglar&gt; &lt;[smeghed]&gt; can you please ask abashi : what happened to the lev 49 pally spell (rangers/sk had them in a long time ago)...and to comment on deepwater helm nerf</EM><BR><BR><STRONG><FONT color=gold>&lt;Abashi&gt;</FONT></STRONG> Smeghed: The quest dialog is designed, the dialog done, and now treasure tables and such have to be built.&nbsp; I *hope* it will only be another week or two.&nbsp; It's a cool spell btw.<BR><BR><STRONG><FONT color=gold>&lt;Abashi&gt;</FONT></STRONG> rofl...<BR><BR><STRONG><FONT color=gold>&lt;Abashi&gt;</FONT></STRONG> Just heard something funny<BR><BR><STRONG><FONT color=gold>&lt;Abashi&gt;</FONT></STRONG> Anyone here have a howling harpoon?<BR><BR><STRONG><FONT color=gold>&lt;Abashi&gt;</FONT></STRONG> The proc was wicked<BR><BR><STRONG><FONT color=gold>&lt;Abashi&gt;</FONT></STRONG> Someone attached dragonbreath to the weapon<BR><BR><STRONG><FONT color=gold>&lt;Abashi&gt;</FONT></STRONG> We'll be nerfing that today btw.</P>
